usage: pvm [-v | --version] [-? | -h | --help] <command> [<args>]

Command:
?|h|help                    Show Help
v|version                   Show Version
l|list (all|py|python)      List out 10 recent/all virtual environment or all version of python
s|search (keyword)          Search virtual environment by keyword
a|activate (venv)           Activate virtual environment
n|new (venv)                Create new virtual environment
d|delete (venv)             Delete virtual environment
i|install (version|l|list)  Install specific version of Python or list of Python that available to download
u|uninstall (version)       Unintall Python

Before use:
1. Download Python and use pip to install virtualenv
2. Add 'alias pvm="source pvm"' to ".bashrc"
3. Change the path in line 2 of pvm to where the program is

Files Tree Diagram:
Directory
  ├─python
  │   ├─Python-3.8.X
  │   ├─Python-2.X.X
  │   └─Python-....
  ├─venv
  │   ├─env01
  │   ├─env02
  │   └─env03
  ├─pvm
  │
  └─README.md

